The paper discusses a method for ontology fault localization, which involves using queries to identify faults in an ontology. This is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), software engineering (cs.SE), databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper specifically discusses the use of expert interactions and optimization criteria, which are common themes in the AI and SE sub-categories. Additionally, the use of queries and fault localization is relevant to the DB and IR sub-categories.
